209template <class T>
210class Local {
211 public:
212 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
213 template <class S>
214 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
215 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
221 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
222 }
223
227 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
228
232 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
233
234 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
235
236 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
237
244 template <class S>
245 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
246 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
247 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
248 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
249 if (b == 0) return false;
250 return *a == *b;
251 }
252
253 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
254 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
255 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
256 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
257 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
258 if (b == 0) return false;
259 return *a == *b;
260 }
261
268 template <class S>
269 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
270 return !operator==(that);
271 }
272
273 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
274 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
275 return !operator==(that);
276 }
277
278 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
279#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
280 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
281 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
282 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
283#endif
284 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
285 }
286
287
288 template <class S> V8_INLINE Local<S> As() {
289 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
290 }
291
297 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
298 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
299 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
300
301 private:
302 friend class Utils;
303 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
304 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
305 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
306 template<class F> friend class Local;
307 template <class F>
308 friend class MaybeLocal;
309 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
310 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
311 friend class String;
312 friend class Object;
313 friend class Context;
314 friend class Private;
315 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
316 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
317 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
318 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
319 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
320 friend class HandleScope;
321 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
322 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
323 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
324 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
325
326 template <class S>
327 V8_INLINE Local(S* that)
328 : val_(that) {}
329 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
330 T* val_;
331};

349template <class T>
350class MaybeLocal {
351 public:
352 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
353 template <class S>
354 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
355 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
356 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
357 }
358
359 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
360
361 template <class S>
362 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
363 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
364 return !IsEmpty();
365 }
366
367 // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
368 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
369
370 template <class S>
371 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
372 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
373 }
374
375 private:
376 T* val_;
377};

380// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.

382 public:

386 Set(isolate, handle);

395 int index_;
396};

402template <typename T>
403class WeakCallbackInfo {
404 public:
405 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
406
407 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
408 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
409 Callback* callback)
410 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
411 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
412 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
413 }
414 }
415
416 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
417 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
418 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
419
420 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
421 void* GetInternalField1()) const {
422 return internal_fields_[0];
423 }
424 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
425 void* GetInternalField2()) const {
426 return internal_fields_[1];
427 }
428
429 bool IsFirstPass() const { return callback_ != nullptr; }
430
431 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
432 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
433 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
434 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
435 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
436 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
437 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
438
439 private:
440 Isolate* isolate_;
441 T* parameter_;
442 Callback* callback_;
443 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
444};

544 template <typename P>
545 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
546 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
547 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
548 typename WeakCallbackData<T, P>::Callback callback));
549
550 template <typename S, typename P>
551 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
552 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
553 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
554 typename WeakCallbackData<S, P>::Callback callback));
555
556 // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
557 // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
558 // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
559 // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
560 // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
561 // fields in the dying object.
562 template <typename P>
563 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
564 "use SetWeak",
565 void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
566 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
567 int internal_field_index1 = -1,
568 int internal_field_index2 = -1));
569
570 template <typename P>
571 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
572 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
573 WeakCallbackType type);
574
575 template<typename P>
576 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
577
578 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
579 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
580
587 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
588
597 V8_INLINE void MarkPartiallyDependent();
598
599 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
600
602 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
603
605 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
606
611 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
612
617 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
618
619 private:
620 friend class Isolate;
621 friend class Utils;
622 template<class F> friend class Local;
623 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
624 template <class F>
625 friend class Global;
626 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
627 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
628 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
629 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
630 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
631 friend class Object;
632
633 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
634 PersistentBase(PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
635 void operator=(PersistentBase&) = delete;
636 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
637
638 T* val_;

689template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
690 public:
694 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
700 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Handle<S> that)
701 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
702 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
703 }
709 template <class S, class M2>
710 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
711 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
712 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
713 }
720 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
721 Copy(that);
722 }
723 template <class S, class M2>
724 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
725 Copy(that);
726 }
727 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
728 Copy(that);
729 return *this;
730 }
731 template <class S, class M2>
732 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
733 Copy(that);
734 return *this;
735 }
741 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
742 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
743 }
744
745 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
746 template <class S>
747 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
748#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
749 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
750 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
751 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
752#endif
753 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(that);
754 }
755
756 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
757 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT
758 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
759 }
760
761 private:
762 friend class Isolate;
763 friend class Utils;
764 template<class F> friend class Local;
765 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
766 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
767
768 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(S* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) { }
769 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
770 template<class S, class M2>
771 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
772};

780template <class T>
781class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
782 public:
786 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
792 template <class S>
793 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Handle<S> that)
794 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {

802 template <class S>
803 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
804 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
805 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
806 }
810 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {

813 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
817 template <class S>
818 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
819 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
820 if (this != &rhs) {
821 this->Reset();
822 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
823 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
824 }
825 return *this;
826 }
830 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); }

835 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;

1102 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1103 enum BufferPolicy {
1104 BufferNotOwned,
1105 BufferOwned
1106 };
1107
1108 CachedData()
1109 : data(NULL),
1110 length(0),
1111 rejected(false),
1112 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1113
1114 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1115 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1116 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1117 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1118 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1119 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1120 ~CachedData();
1121 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1122 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1123 const uint8_t* data;
1124 int length;
1125 bool rejected;
1126 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1127
1128 private:
1129 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1130 CachedData(const CachedData&);
1131 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1132 };

2404 // Note that symbols created this way are never collected, so
2405 // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.

4840struct JitCodeEvent {
4841 enum EventType {
4842 CODE_ADDED,
4843 CODE_MOVED,
4844 CODE_REMOVED,
4845 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
4846 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
4847 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
4848 };
4849 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
4850 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
4851 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
4852 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
4853 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
4854 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
4855
4856 // Type of event.
4857 EventType type;
4858 // Start of the instructions.
4859 void* code_start;
4860 // Size of the instructions.
4861 size_t code_len;
4862 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
4863 Handle<UnboundScript> script;
4864 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
4865 // code line information which is returned from the
4866 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
4867 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
4868 void* user_data;
4869
4870 struct name_t {
4871 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
4872 // zero-terminated.
4873 const char* str;
4874 // Number of chars in str.
4875 size_t len;
4876 };
4877
4878 struct line_info_t {
4879 // PC offset
4880 size_t offset;
4881 // Code postion
4882 size_t pos;
4883 // The position type.
4884 PositionType position_type;
4885 };
4886
4887 union {
4888 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
4889 struct name_t name;
4890
4891 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
4892 struct line_info_t line_info;
4893
4894 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
4895 void* new_code_start;
4896 };
4897};

4905 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
4906};

6052template <class T>
6053class Maybe {
6054 public:
6055 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6056 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6057
6058 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6059 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6060 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6061 return value;
6062 }
6063
6064 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6065 return has_value ? value : default_value;
6066 }
6067
6068 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6069 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6070 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6071 }
6072
6073 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6074 return !operator==(other);
6075 }
6076
6077 private:
6078 Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6079 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6080
6081 bool has_value;
6082 T value;
6083
6084 template <class U>
6085 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6086 template <class U>
6087 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6088};
6089
6090
6091template <class T>
6092inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6093 return Maybe<T>();
6094}
6095
6096
6097template <class T>
6098inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6099 return Maybe<T>(t);
6100}

6578const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6579const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6580const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6581
6582// Tag information for HeapObject.
6583const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6584const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6585const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6586
6587// Tag information for Smi.
6588const int kSmiTag = 0;
6589const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6590const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6591
6592template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6593
6594template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6595V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6596 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6597 uintptr_t tagged_value =
6598 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6599 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6600}
6601
6602// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6603template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
6604 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
6605 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6606 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6607 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6608 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6609 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
6610 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
6611 }
6612 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6613 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6614 }
6615 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6616 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
6617 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
6618 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
6619 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
6620 //
6621 // CAUTION: The original code below:
6622 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
6623 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
6624 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
6625 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
6626 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
6627 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
6628 }
6629};
6630
6631// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
6632template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
6633 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
6634 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6635 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6636 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6637 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6638 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
6639 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
6640 }
6641 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6642 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6643 }
6644 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6645 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
6646 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
6647 }
6648};
6649
6650typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
6651const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
6652const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
6653V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
6654V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

6760 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
6761 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6762 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);

6765 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
6766 bool value, int shift) {
6767 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6768 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
6769 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
6770 }

6772 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {

6774 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;

6777 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
6778 uint8_t value) {
6779 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6780 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
6781 }

6811 template <typename T>
6812 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
6813 typedef internal::Object O;
6814 typedef internal::Internals I;
6815 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
6816 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
6817 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
6818 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
6819 int value_offset =
6820 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
6821 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
6822 }

7076}

7079void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
7080 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
7081 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
7082}

7084template<typename T>
7085void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
7086 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7087 typedef internal::Internals I;
7088 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
7089 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
7090 return;
7091 }
7092 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
7093}
7094
7095template<typename T>
7096void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
7097 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7098 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
7099 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
7100 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
7101 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
7102 return;
7103 }
7104 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
7105}

7107template<typename T>

7109 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
7110 typedef internal::Internals I;
7111 int root_index;
7112 if (value) {
7113 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
7114 } else {
7115 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
7116 }
7117 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
7118}

7299
7300Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
7301#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7302 typedef internal::Object O;
7303 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7304 typedef internal::Internals I;
7305 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7306 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7307 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7308 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
7309 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7310 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
7311 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
7312 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7313 }
7314#endif
7315 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
7316}
7317
7318
7319void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
7320#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7321 typedef internal::Object O;
7322 typedef internal::Internals I;
7323 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7324 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7325 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7326 if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
7327 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7328 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
7329 }
7330#endif
7331 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
7332}

7352String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
7353 typedef internal::Object O;
7354 typedef internal::Internals I;
7355 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7356 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
7357 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
7358 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7359 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
7360 } else {
7361 result = NULL;
7362 }
7363#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7364 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
7365#endif
7366 return result;
7367}

7369
7370String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
7371 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
7372 typedef internal::Object O;
7373 typedef internal::Internals I;
7374 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7375 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
7376 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
7377 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
7378 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
7379 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
7380 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7381 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
7382 }
7383#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7384 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
7385#endif
7386 return resource;

7825
7826int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
7827 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
7828 typedef internal::Internals I;
7829 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
7830 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7831 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
7832 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
7833 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
7834 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7835 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
7836 int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
7837 if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
7838 amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
7839 I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
7840 CollectAllGarbage("external memory allocation limit reached.");
7841 }
7842 *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
